Interface LikeStatisticRepository

All Superinterfaces:
org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<LikeStatistic,Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<LikeStatistic,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<LikeStatistic,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<LikeStatistic,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<LikeStatistic,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<LikeStatistic>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<LikeStatistic,Long>
public interface LikeStatisticRepository extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<LikeStatistic,Long>
Repository interface for managing LikeStatistic entities.

This interface extends JpaRepository and provides methods for performing CRUD operations on LikeStatistic entities. It includes custom query methods to find like statistics based on the statistic date.

Key Features:

  • Find like statistics by a specific statistic date.
  • Retrieve an Optional of like statistics for a given statistic date.
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Mukhammed Lolo

    • findByStatisticDate

      LikeStatistic findByStatisticDate(LocalDate statisticDate)
      Finds a like statistic by its statistic date.

      This method searches for the like statistic associated with the given date.

      Parameters:
      statisticDate - the date for which to retrieve the like statistic
      Returns:
      the like statistic for the given date, or null if no statistic exists

    • getByStatisticDate

      Optional<LikeStatistic> getByStatisticDate(LocalDate statisticDate)
      Retrieves an Optional of a like statistic by its statistic date.

      This method returns an Optional containing the like statistic if it exists for the specified date, or an empty Optional if no statistic is found.

      Parameters:
      statisticDate - the date for which to retrieve the like statistic
      Returns:
      an Optional containing the like statistic, or Optional.empty() if no statistic exists
